# Cloudflare Pages routing (emitted to the build output root by the Pages build).
#
# Precedence at request time: Pages Functions (root _middleware proxies /api/*,
# sitemap, site.webmanifest to the origin; /map/:id and /search/:query inject OG
# tags) run FIRST, then real static files (/assets/*, robots.txt, ...), then these
# rules. So the rules below only fire for paths none of the above handled.

# Legacy client-side redirect pages: they read old /map?id=NNN and /map#NNN URLs
# (fragments never reach the server, so this must stay client-side) and forward to
# /map/{id}. Kept for backwards compatibility; candidates for removal later.
/map        /map-redirect.html      200
/replay     /replay-redirect.html   200

# SPA fallback: every remaining route renders the shell and the SolidJS router
# takes over (/, /upload, /about, /user/:name, /login, /moderation, bare /search).
/*          /index.html             200
